The paper deals with compressing convolutional neural networks for image feature extraction, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of reinforcement learning and knowledge distillation also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between speed, memory, and accuracy, which could fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of compression techniques to reduce the size of neural networks is also relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
